The paper deals with the optimization of deep neural network accelerators, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of approximate computing and multiobjective optimization algorithms also suggests a connection to computer architecture (cs.AR) and control systems (cs.SY). The proposed approach involves the selection of suitable approximate multipliers, which can be seen as a problem in electronic design automation (cs.ET) and the optimization of energy consumption, which is related to energy management (cs.EM).
